{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/sprinting-on-georeplication","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"6ea11761-ee11-5694-9b9a-f28b65fa9a18","html":"<h2 id=\"what-is-ibm-event-streams\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#what-is-ibm-event-streams\" aria-label=\"what is ibm event streams permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>What is IBM Event Streams?</h2>\n<p>IBM Event Streams is IBMâ€™s Apache Kafka offering. Apache Kafka is an immensely popular messaging software which was released by the Apache foundation in 2011. The Event Streams team provide Kafka as software and as a service and add fully supported capabilities such as an award-winning UI, schema registry, REST API and connector library.</p>\n<h3 id=\"my-role\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#my-role\" aria-label=\"my role permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>My role</h3>\n<p>User Experience Designer</p>\n<h3 id=\"objectives\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#objectives\" aria-label=\"objectives permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Objectives</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Enable IT Administrators and Developers to connect their applications with Event Streams.</li>\n<li>Maintain a current User Experience within the IBM Design Language that is consistent with other IBM products.</li>\n<li>Plan the future of Event Streams and organise the Event Streams roadmap competitively.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"summary\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#summary\" aria-label=\"summary permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Summary</h3>\n<p>Messages (events) travelling through, are the core of the Event Streams (Kafka) concept. Following user feedback that our message browser consumed a lot of resources, we redesigned it to achieve the same value in a much lighter way.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/sprinting-on-georeplication","tagSlugs":["/tag/ux/","/tag/design/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2020-02-01T22:40:32.169Z","description":"Messages travelling through, are the core of the Event Strea